That I have perused a Gaelic manuscript, containing all the poems translated by Mr Maepherson, or a considerable part of them, I am not able to say; but can honestly af- firm, that I have seen a Gaelic manuscript in the hands of an old hard, who travelled about through the Highlands and Isles about thirty years ago, out of which he read, in my hearing, and before thousands yet alive, the exploits of Cuchullin, Fingal, Oscar, Ossian, Gaul, Dermid, and the other heroes celebrated in Mr Maepherson's book.

The name of the tribe which produced these he- reditary poets and shenachies‚ was Macmhurich.
